  "A school surveys 200 students about their preferred lunch option (Pizza or Salad) and their grade (Freshman or Senior). The results show 80 Freshmen chose Pizza, 20 Freshmen chose Salad, 50 Seniors chose Pizza, and 50 Seniors chose Salad. What is the joint frequency of Seniors who chose Salad?": "",
  "50": "",
  "80": "",
  "The joint frequency for Seniors choosing Salad is 50, as it is the count in the cell where the Senior row and Salad column intersect.": "",
  "A company surveys 150 employees about transportation to work (Car or Public Transit) and department (Engineering or Marketing). Engineering: 40 Car, 30 Transit. Marketing: 50 Car, 30 Transit. What fraction of Marketing employees use public transit?": "",
  "50/80": "",
  "30/150": "",
  "30/80": "",
  "30/60": "",
  "The conditional frequency is the joint frequency for Marketing + Transit (30) divided by the Marketing total (50 + 30 = 80), giving 30/80 = 37.5%.": "",
  "A sports club surveys 120 members about their preferred activity (Swimming or Tennis) and membership type (Monthly or Annual). Monthly: 25 Swimming, 35 Tennis. Annual: 40 Swimming, 20 Tennis. Is there an association between membership type and preferred activity?": "",
