  "Cannot be determined from this data": "",
  "No, because the totals are different": "",
  "No, the conditional distributions are the same": "",
  "Monthly: 35/60 = 58% prefer Tennis. Annual: 40/60 = 67% prefer Swimming. Since the conditional distributions differ, there is an association between membership type and activity preference.": "",
  "A hospital tracks patient satisfaction (Satisfied or Unsatisfied) by ward (A or B). Ward A: 70 Satisfied, 30 Unsatisfied. Ward B: 45 Satisfied, 55 Unsatisfied. What is the marginal frequency of satisfied patients?": "",
